  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with Stage IV obstructing colorectal cancer and unresectable liver metastses, with
      general and local conditions not a risk for coliorectal resection, will be randomized to have
      either endoscopic stenting or colorectal resection
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with obstructing colorectal cancer, Stage IV with not resectable metastases will be
      considered .

      Patients with acceptable general and local conditions, to allow a safe surgical resection
      will be considered.

      Patients will be randomized to have endoscopic stenting or colorectal resection.

      All patients will receive postoperative chemio therapy
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
